name: Shaolin Graffiti Monks Wu in Green
description: Japanese pirates known as the Wokou raided China's Eastern and Southeastern coasts on an unprecedented scale killing many under the orders of the Tokugawa Shogunate. The Shaolin Monks were called on by the Emperor of China to assist in the fight. The pirates were beaten, but many monks lost their lives. Four monks, Wu, Chu, Sun, and Tenzen, were captured and taken to Japan but were able to escape. They vowed to bring down the Shogunate. Later, teaming up with a young Samuari named Kendo, they journeyed to Edo to face Tokugawa! Along the way, the monks taught many. Their religion of Graffiti-Zen represents oneness through the arts.
